OL,7,FThis included rulings on whether 22
OL,8,Fpeople did die during the attack, and
OL,9,Fwhether the Hibberts' injuries were
OL,10,Fcaused by the bombing.
OL,12,FJudge Richard Davison said: "Suffice
OL,13,Fit to say that, although his beliefs
OL,14,Fmay be genuinely held, his theory that
OL,15,Fthe Manchester bombing was an
OL,16,Foperation staged by government
OL,17,Fagencies in which no-one was genuinely
OL,18,Fkilled or injured is absurd and
OL,19,Ffantastical and it provides no basis
OL,20,Fto rebut the conviction."
